@startuml
title Mention with Task Context + Message Reference

participant "Discord Client" as DC
participant "mention.py" as MH
participant "database.py" as DB
participant "prompts.py" as PR
participant "Provider (AI)" as AI
participant "tool/task" as TT

== User replies to a bot notification ==

DC -> DC: Detect message.reference
DC -> DC: Fetch referenced message\n(bot's notification)
DC -> DC: Truncate to 2000 chars
DC -> MH: on_mention(content, channel_id,\nuser_id, history, referenced_content)

== Load context ==

MH -> DB: load_summary(user_id, channel_id)
DB --> MH: memory_summary

MH -> DB: load_turns(user_id, channel_id)
DB --> MH: stored_turns

MH -> DB: get_pending_tasks_summary(user_id)
DB --> MH: task_summary

MH -> PR: build_system_prompt(\ntool_hints, memory_summary, task_summary)
PR --> MH: system_prompt

MH -> MH: _build_user_prompt(\ncontent, stored_turns,\nhistory, referenced_content)

== Tool-call loop ==

MH -> AI: chat(messages)
AI --> MH: tool_call: task.list()

MH -> TT: execute(action="list")
TT -> DB: list_tasks(user_id)
DB --> TT: tasks
TT --> MH: formatted task list

MH -> AI: chat(messages + tool_result)
AI --> MH: text response

MH -> DB: save_turn(user, assistant)
MH --> DC: reply text

@enduml
